						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">bazz wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Now, one of the most important things you could do is establish an official MetaSprite format.</div><br />Different metasprite formats are better for different games. For example, cut scenes in Concentration Room for NES use horizontal or vertical strips of 8x8 pixel tiles with the same color set byte and tile numbers 1 apart (horizontally) or 16 apart (vertically).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">btw, what game is your avatar from?</div><br />Paste the URL of Espozo's avatar into Google Search, click Search, click Search by image, and the result is &quot;Best guess for this image: metal slug boss&quot;. I put in my current avatar and I get <a href="http://centopercentomamma.it/costume-carnevale-last-minute-di-peppa-pig/" class="postlink">Peppa Freaking Pig</a>.</div>

